Mareppa Naik Mogdampur, president of the Yadgir district Valmiki Naik Sangha, has said that the sangha will stage a protest outside the Regional Commissionerâ€™s Office here on Monday and demand that action be taken against officials of the Revenue Department for allegedly issuing fake caste certificates to people for getting jobs.AllegationIn a statement here on Friday, Mr. Mogdampur said that many people belonging to non-Scheduled Tribes communities were given fake caste certificates mentioning their caste as belonging to Scheduled Tribes by Revenue authorities in Kalaburagi, Bidar, Yadgir, Raichur, Koppal and Ballari districts.Such people are presently working in various government departments.But, no action had been taken against those responsible for such a situation, though several requisitions had been given earlier, he said.Therefore, the Valmiki Naik community will stage a protest against such an illegal act and urge the Regional Commissioner to take immediate action, he said.Many who got such certificates are working in various depts,says sangha